# reset moves the branch head and restores the working directory to a commit.
I definitions.inc
> init
<<<
+ wug.txt wug.txt
> add wug.txt
<<<
> commit "v1"
<<<
> log
===
${COMMIT_HEAD}
v1

===
${COMMIT_HEAD}
initial commit

<<<*
# Capture the initial commit id (2nd captured group).
D INIT_ID "${2}"
+ wug.txt notwug.txt
> add wug.txt
<<<
> commit "v2"
<<<
= wug.txt notwug.txt
# Reset back to the initial commit removes tracked wug.txt.
> reset ${INIT_ID}
<<<
* wug.txt
> status
=== Branches ===
\*master

=== Staged Files ===

=== Removed Files ===

=== Modifications Not Staged For Commit ===

=== Untracked Files ===

<<<*
